
SNAIL : Put a snail in your shell

   - Search and prints the station's informations
   - Prints the next trains on a station

Requirements :

   1) Get the stations's list from SNCF's OpenData web site : https://ressources.data.sncf.com/explore/dataset/sncf-gares-et-arrets-transilien-ile-de-france/?tab=metas
   > curl -o stations.csv  https://ressources.data.sncf.com/explore/dataset/sncf-gares-et-arrets-transilien-ile-de-france/download/?format=csv&timezone=Europe/Berlin

   2) Snail uses open one API from SNCF. In order to use Snail, you should ask an ID for this API to SNCF. See this page for more informations : https://ressources.data.sncf.com/explore/dataset/api-temps-reel-transilien/?tab=metas
      Then you can configure your's snail by adding your login / password to this file : modules/settings.py


Usage :

   0) Init the database :

   > snail init --file stations.csv


   1) Search and prints the stations's informations :

   > snail find rungis
   87546291  RUNGIS LA FRATERNELLE                                   SNCF (48.7402800868 / 2.35276043346)   4
   87546192  PONT DE RUNGIS AÃ©roport d'Orly                          SNCF (48.7478708023 / 2.37293264591)   4


   2) Prints the next trains on a station :

   > snail station 87546192
   87546192  PONT DE RUNGIS Aeroport d'Orly                          SNCF (48.7478708023 / 2.37293264591)   4

   22 train(s)
   23/03/2015 11:23 [R]  142596  NORA  PONTOISE
   23/03/2015 11:38 [R]  141589  MONA  MASSY PALAISEAU
   23/03/2015 11:38 [R]  148102  GOTA  MONTIGNY BEAUCHAMP

